title.narrative: Scaling up of interventions to combat tuberculosis in Côte d'Ivoire

description.narrative: Côte d'Ivoire - Tuberculosis - Ministry of Health, Public Hygiene and Universal Health Coverage of the Republic of Côte d’Ivoire - MOH - PNLT. This program has the following goals: Reduce the mortality rate due to TB by 20 percent between 2015 and 2020.. The objectives of this program are: Increase case notification of new and relapse cases from 21,357 in 2016 to 22,795 in 2020. By 2020 (2019 cohort) achieve a treatment success rate of 87 percent among new and relapse cases. Increase the proportion of TB patients tested for HIV from 98 percent in 2016 to 100 percent from 2018 and the proportion of TB/HIV patients treated with ART from 90 percent in 2015 to 100 percent by 2018. Increase the treatment success rate among those treated for multidrug-resistant TB (MDR-TB) from 81 percent in 2015 to 86 percent by 2020. Improve and strengthen the NTCP’s technical, management and coordination capacities
